# Simple Arduino Projects for Beginners

## Complete Component Guide for Independent Team Projects

---

## 1. Single LED Blink

**What it does:** This is the absolute beginner's first project - the "Hello World" of electronics. A single LED connected to the Arduino turns on for one second, then turns off for one second, and repeats this pattern continuously. This simple project introduces students to the basics of electronic circuits, Arduino programming, and the concept of digital output. It's the perfect starting point for anyone new to electronics and coding.

**Real-world applications:**

- Indicator lights in appliances
- Warning lights on electronic devices
- Status indicators on routers and modems
- Blinking lights on emergency vehicles

**Learning outcomes:**

- Understanding basic circuits (LED, resistor, power)
- Digital output control (HIGH/LOW states)
- Introduction to Arduino IDE and code uploading
- Basic programming concepts (loops, delays)
- Proper LED polarity and resistor usage

**Difficulty Level:** Beginner

**Recommended for:** Classes 4-5

**Project Duration:** 30 minutes - 45 minutes

|Component|Quantity|Specifications/Notes|Search Term for Amazon|Approx. Price (INR)|
|---|---|---|---|---|
|Arduino Uno|1|With USB cable|"Arduino Uno R3"|₹400-600|
|LED (Any Color)|1|5mm|"5mm LED Assorted"|₹5-10|
|Resistor|1|220Ω|"220 Ohm Resistor"|₹5-10|
|Breadboard|1|400 points|"Breadboard 400 points"|₹80-150|
|Jumper Wires|1 pack|Male-to-male (minimum 10 pieces)|"Arduino Jumper Wires"|₹80-150|
