## 3. Night Light (Auto Light Sensor)

**What it does:** This intelligent lighting system automatically detects ambient light levels using an LDR (Light Dependent Resistor) sensor. When the room becomes dark (like during evening or when you cover the sensor), the LED automatically turns on. When there's sufficient light, it turns off. Students can adjust sensitivity using a potentiometer to control at what darkness level the light should activate. This demonstrates smart automation and energy-saving concepts.

**Real-world applications:**

- Automatic street lights
- Garden and pathway lighting
- Home automation systems
- Energy-saving office lighting
- Night lights for bedrooms and hallways

**Learning outcomes:**

- Understanding analog sensors and light detection
- Reading analog values (0-1023 range)
- Threshold-based decision making
- Automatic control systems
- Energy conservation concepts

**Difficulty Level:** Beginner-Intermediate

**Recommended for:** Classes 5-7

**Project Duration:** 1-2 hours

|Component|Quantity|Specifications/Notes|Search Term for Amazon|Approx. Price (INR)|
|---|---|---|---|---|
|Arduino Uno|1|With USB cable|"Arduino Uno R3"|₹400-600|
|LDR Sensor|1|Light Dependent Resistor|"LDR Sensor Module"|₹30-60|
|LED (White/Bright)|3|5mm or LED strip|"5mm White LED" or "LED Strip"|₹30-100|
|Resistor (for LDR)|1|10kΩ|"10K Ohm Resistor"|₹5-10|
|Resistor (for LED)|3|220Ω|"220 Ohm Resistor Pack"|₹20-40|
|Potentiometer|1|10kΩ for sensitivity adjustment|"10K Potentiometer"|₹20-40|
|Breadboard|1|400/830 points|"Breadboard 830 points"|₹80-150|
|Jumper Wires|1 pack|Male-to-male (minimum 20 pieces)|"Arduino Jumper Wires"|₹80-150|
