## 7. Mission Impossible Timer

**What it does:** Inspired by the famous Mission Impossible movie countdown scenes, this project creates a dramatic countdown timer that displays time on a display screen. When activated by pressing a button, it counts down from 60 seconds (or any set time). As time runs out, a red LED blinks faster and faster, and a buzzer beeps with increasing urgency. When the timer reaches zero, the buzzer sounds continuously and the red LED stays on - "Mission Failed!" A reset button allows you to start the countdown again. This project is exciting and teaches time-based programming.

**Real-world applications:**

- Kitchen cooking timers
- Exam countdown timers
- Sports training interval timers
- Industrial process timers
- Game show countdown displays

**Learning outcomes:**

- Time-based programming and countdown logic
- Display interfacing (7-segment or LCD)
- Variable speed control (accelerating beeps)
- Button interrupt handling
- Creating dramatic user experiences

**Difficulty Level:** Intermediate

**Recommended for:** Classes 7-9

**Project Duration:** 2-3 hours

|Component|Quantity|Specifications/Notes|Search Term for Amazon|Approx. Price (INR)|
|---|---|---|---|---|
